cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a method for semi-supervised learning for text classification tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel scalable method for deep neural networks (DNNs), which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The method involves imitator networks, which could also relate to computer vision tasks, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of scarcity of labeled data, which could be addressed using techniques from cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
